Have you noticed that usually one of your nostril's is more active than the other? 🤔

My left nostril is active right now. Check yours right now and keep reading to know what it means! 🙆🏻‍♀️

Both left and right nostril play a specific role in managing your energies. The dominant nostril keeps on changing throughout the day depending on the activity that you're doing. 

The right nostril is called Pingala and its role is to generate heat in the body. It propels you into action, keeps you focused and helps you achieve your goals. An imbalanced Pingala can lead to aggression, stress and hyperactivity.✅️

 The left nostril is called Ida and its role is to cool down the body. It brings relaxation, promotes creativity and aids in healing. An imbalanced Ida can lead to lethargy, self doubt and poor self control.✅️

 To keep your system balanced, you can start your mornings with pranayama to balance both the nostrils and live a fulfilling day.🥳

What you need to do instead is to strengthen your thighs and calf muscles. This way your knees will not be forced to take your weight and will not deteriorate further.

In yoga we never put strain on our face. 
Because where there is strain, there can never be peace. 😛

The same holds true for our daily lives. People who scowl or frown all the time tend to have more turmoil within. 😶‍🌫️

The moment we ease our faces, we experience an ease within ourselves too. 😊

Try and keep the edges of your lips always up rather than down. This will keep a gentle smile on your face. 😄

Whenever you notice that your forehead has lines, ease the forehead and relax. 🙄

This will help you stay grounded as well at ease. It may be difficult in the beginning but over time you will cultivate a new powerful habit! ✅️

Hathyogapradipikā states that death can be averted after six months' practice of Uddiyanabandha.

 According to Hathyogapradipikā, Uddiyanabandha changes the course of the downward moving Apāna Vayu and pulls it upwards. Combined with Jalandharabandha, Prana is locked in navel center. In the navel center, Prāna and Apäna are united with Samana. The union of these two opposite energies of Apana and Prana in the navel region results into an explosion of potential force which travels upward through Nāḍī. This force is then powered by Udana Vayu and is taken up to the higher centers. Udḍīyanabandha improves blood circulation in the trunk and strengthens all the internal organs. 
All abdominal organs are toned, massaged and strengthened. Therefore, ailments related to abdomen and digestion including constipation, indigestion and diabetes can be cured. It also strengthens respiratory muscles as squeezing of lungs during Uddiyanabandha increases the gaseous exchange. It also alleviates depression, dullness and lethargy. 

Precautions:-
 Anyone who suffers from stomach or intestinal ulcers, hernia, high blood pressure, heart disease, glaucoma or raised intracranial pressure must not practise this bandha.
Avoid this during pregnancy too.

In yoga, we don't measure our success by our bank balance, or our relationship status. We see how balanced we are in our thinking and emotions. 
When left side is more stable your feminine energy is more active. The characteristics associated with this are-
- Intuitive
-Nurturing
- Dynamic
- Creative
- Resilient
- Empathetic
-Affectionate
- Bold

When right side is more dominant, you're more likely to display masculine characteristics such as -
-Stable 
- Giving
- Independent 
- Logical
-Rational
- Organised
- Minimalistic
- Meditative

As per the yogic tradition, we're all a mix of Masculine (Shiva) and Feminine (Shakti). When these energies are balanced, we feel more harmonious within and are efficient in the outer world as well.

To balance these energies, we suggest practising yogasanas and pranayama everyday. Having a routine, building a regular exercise practice and eating healthy will help you keep your energies stable.

A fluid that helps keep the vagina clean and infection-free, vaginal discharge is completely natural. But its color, texture, and amount can differ, depending on your age and where you are in your menstrual cycle.

Some changes, however, can be a sign of an underlying health condition. These can include significant color or odor changes as well as a difference in consistency.

When to visit a doctor
If you're ever worried about your vaginal discharge, talk with a clinician as soon as possible. This is particularly true if your discharge changes color, smell, or consistency or if you're noticing more of it than usual.

Kagasana is a simple sitting pose in which you are sitting with your bend knees and folding hands to cover your knees.
If you do this pose in the morning with empty stomach then this pose helps you a lot.

Precautions-
*Don't have hunched back while holding this pose*

1) If you feel Uncomfortable while sitting then try to avoid this pose.

2) The person has critical Back pain or has cervical issues, they should also leave this pose.

3) You will use the support (wall, cushion) to do this pose.

4) Back pain, Hernia patients must not do this pose because it will lead to some serious injury.

5) Pregnant women should avoid Kagasana because this pose directly affects the stomach.

1.Bathing after meals? 
Never do this again please :)

We are eating something, and as soon as we are eating, the fire is lighting up inside our body, and it burn max in the intial stage of digestion, and if we are bathing immediately after it, we can never save ourselves from digestive disorders

So bathing always empty stomach :) or with minimum gap of 1.5 hours.

2. Exercising after food?
A big NO!
Modern nutritionist say that you need that energy for workout which comes from food but the results will be in front of you in long run which will lead to sluggish metabolism in the long run
why?
Because all the energy of the body is going towards digestion of the food and at the same time we are working hard on our health as well, which will lead to the depletion of energy/charm of body in long run.
That's what yoga and Ayurveda says:)

Still if you wanna eat( once a week) cook it in a lil oil in cumin and rock salt :) and now enjoy
A big no for people with gastric issue and who have skin issues and vata type!

5. why no tea and coffee?

It can lead to heartburn, bloating, pain and ulcers
This is because the acid in tea/coffee based drinks interfere with the digestive acids in the stomach and lead to bloating and acid reflux.
And so many skin issues as well!

Most of us have messed up BREATHING Pattern. Our belly & lungs should EXPAND as we breathe in and should contract as we breathe out. Place a hand on your belly right now and check if it's true for you or not.

If you are doing the reverse, than ABDOMINAL Breathing is a good starting point. As you INHALE - Expand your Belly and as you EXHALE - Your Belly should go inwards. But this is just ABDOMINAL BREATHING.

YOGIC BREATHING has 3 parts - ABDOMINAL, THORACIC AND

CLAVICULAR.

As you INHALE - You first need to fill up your belly, then inhale into your ribs and then upper back, shoulders & all the way upto throat. Basically INHALE - Down to Up.

And as you EXHALE - First Empty your throat, shoulders, lungs and then in the end exhale air out of your belly.

But many people just breathe from Belly and not use the lungs.

Just think about it, if we were to not use lungs, why would God give us LUNGS, the primary organ of the respiratory system.

Breathing only from belly means you are not letting the lungs do it's primary job & when we don't use it, we lose it. In short, only abdominal breathing will weakens our respiratory system by reducing the lung capacity.

So basically read the labels while choosing the products the cleaner and lesser ingredients is better
